snippet.textDisplay:
Are you afraid of Death in a time like this?
If you are you have come to the right place. Not only will you be comforted, but you will be free from death itself completly!
When you see a painting....you know no doubt there was a painter. When you see a building...you know no doubt that there was a builder. And when you see a creation...you know no doubt there was a creator.
When we know there is a creator, we need to do 3 simple things...
Find out who he is
Find out what he wants
And do what he says

But we need to start off with ourselves first.
God made laws...but we broke them
Some of his laws are...
Don't Lie
Don't Steal
Dont say his name in vain
And he also says that "anyone who looks at a woman lustfully has already committed adultery with her in his heart."
Matthew 5:28

We broke these laws are are in grave danger...we have fear of death because we sin against God. And his punishment for sin is Eternal Hell
Hell is a place of torment, a place of eternal fire, a blazing furnace and pain forever.
If you commit a crime and you have to go to court...you are in fear.
Suppose that you robbed a bank and you have to go to court for a trail and you get a 80,000 fine or 25 years in prison. Very scary thing to think about. Now suppose that there is a man there who stands up and says "I'll pay your fine" and gives the judge 80,000 dollars. Now the judge can say "you committed this deadly crime, but you are now free to go."
You did absolutely nothing to deserve it, but you are now free.

God also gave us a free ticket out...be we must know how to unlock the door...and I'll give you the key...

1) We sinned just like the man who robbed the bank
2) We must either pay ourselves, or find someone who can pay for us
3) If we pay...God says that "the wages of sin is death"
If we pay...we pay by going to the prison of hell.
Just like if the man had to pay...he would go to prison for 25 years.
5) But God came down to earth 2,000 years ago, known as Jesus and lived a perfect sinless life and died on the cross for our sins. His last words were, "It is finished" which means the debt has been paid!
6) We are that guilty robber in the court room but Jesus paid the fine for our sins, so now he can let us go freely into heaven!

God tells us exaclty how to recieve this free gift
"If you declare with your mouth, “Jesus is Lord,” and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved."
Romans 10:9

You need to repent of your sin (turn away from your sins and tell God you are sorry) and follow Jesus and you will never ever have fear of death again because now you are on your way to Heaven!

Trust God like you would a parachute...if you are going to jump from a plane 10,000 feet up...the ONLY thing you would trust to save you is your parachute. You would never trust yourself by flapping your arms...It would never work.
Jesus is your parachute...put him on and fully trust him!
Trying to do good works to be saved is like flapping your arms to save yourself while skydiving.

For the Wages of Sin is Death, but the GIFT of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.
Romans 6:23

Start reading the book John and then Romans in the Bible. Pray before you read and God will reveal himself to you!
